			"text": "Hallipterus excelsior comes from the Middle Devonian, with fossils found from around New York and Pennsylvania (USA). It is a large hardieopterid eurypterid, growing up to 1.5 m in length. The carapace is notably tri-angular in shape, with it being much longer than it is wide, adorned with two small eyes separated by a prominent marginal rim, as well as both being partially surrounded by a smaller circular rim."
